In an ideal case, charge should not penetrate through the dielectric material. However, large current flows through it upon applying potential, which is designated as dielectric loss. The dielectric loss versus frequency plot (Fig. S6) suggested minimal dielectric loss and storage of charges in the dielectric material, BHSHNI. As AC conductivity and dielectric loss are closely related, the increase in conductivity will increase the eddy current, which in turn will increase the dielectric loss.45 AC conductivity was calculated using Eq. 3 and was plotted against semi logarithm of angular momentum as depicted in Fig. 3c. The AC conductivity of BHSHNI was found to be ~ 15,000 nΩ−1 cm−1 at higher frequencies.3σAC=ωεoεrtanδ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
